OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FAfter a bright, sunny start,
OL,6,Fcloud will increase through the
OL,7,Fmorning. Showers move in from the
OL,8,Fnorth around midday, clearing by late
OL,9,Fafternoon with the odd sunny intervals
OL,10,Fdeveloping. Breezy, particularly on
OL,11,Fcoasts, and feeling cool in the
OL,12,Fnortherly winds.
OL,13,
OL,14,CTonight:FSunny spells developing
OL,15,Fthrough the evening, though it will
OL,16,Ffeel cool in a northerly breeze.
OL,17,FLargely dry overnight, aside from
OL,18,Fisolated coastal showers, with a frost
OL,19,Fdeveloping in prone spots.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
